caption: My favorite spot for American food. Entered near eleven, it wasn't packed. Service is consistently above par. Prices that are reasonable.
american food, super good. The service was very welcoming and sociable. Bring your appetite because portions are generous.

I love the salad bar, it is excellent! The themed meals that correspond to the show are really fun and I always appreciate the plant based option. It may not be a very affordable restaurant but it is a nice treat.
Run now!  The Golden Girls Drag DIVA Brunch!! A perfect blend of brunch and fabulousness.
The server was attentive; the bus-boys always had our water full and the chef clearly did a great job. The portions don't appear that large, but it's extremely rich food so you'll fill up quickly.
Food was so so.  Service was great.  Salad soup bar is superb.  Fish was good but very  dry.
Salad plates not available.  We had to use snall bread plate.  By the time they restocked we had to catch the show. Food ok..
Great food and drinks
Went with family before a show at the Straz.   Food was flavorless and expensive.  Service took forever.   At $48 a person,  you would expect better.
good selecting of food and friendly service
Nice facility, food at the right temperature but not a great selection of food
Fantastic food!!

Great, the waiter spilled food on my white suit on March 1st the night I saw Hamilton. The managers were great the cleared the stain from my suit and was not noticeable afterwards and gave me his car for the dry cleaning  bill. They were do great, I did not bother them at the bill. Because of them I had a great time. Oh the food was delicious.  I  definitely will be taking my house guests there.

It started bad from the time we arrived for our 5 PM reservation. We arrived at 4:55 PM to find the staff was in a meeting at the bar. Meeting broke and the staff began table preparation and the bartender began cleaning the bar. We are still in the reception area waiting to be seated. At 5:30 PM a young lady came and asked if we would like to be seated. Restaurant was 30 minutes late for it's first reservation. This was a first for me!  The dinning room  looked pleasant with the salad bar in the middle, staff smartly dressed and attentive.  Our waiter Wes greeted us and since  we have never been to the restaurant  he explained the protocol.Buffet style soup and salad, then a choice of one of six entrees and one of four dessert.  Wes was GREAT, he took our drink orders and we were off to the buffet. Choice of two soups...cream of mushroom and seafood bisque. Both soups were delicious. mixed greens or spinach for the salad. Meat tray, cheese tray, fruit, olives, crackers, humus, and four dressing choices.  NICE SO FAR RIGHT?  Then come the entrees.....Between the six people at our table we had all of the entree choices covered. Sirloin steak, Meat loaf, Snapper, Chilean Sea Bass, Chicken breast, and the Chef's Choice... Pork Chop. My daughter was performing in the show at the theater so she was a little pressed for time (ESPECIALLY AFTER WE WERE SEATED 30 Minutes after our reservation time)  but Wes assured us that there would be no problem getting her food first so she could be back stage on time.  Wes didn't lie....her food was out in a flash...( Meat Loaf ). I even commented on how fast the food was produced. I justified to myself thinking " How long does it take to plate a meat loaf " mash potatoes and broccoli?  Meat loaf was OK although the meat loaf at the Barrymore hotel across the street, was ten times better.  Turns out that the meat loaf was the best of class of all the meals served. Sirloin was second, Snapper, Chicken, Chilean Sea Bass, and coming in last was the "Chefs SPECIAL" Pork Chop.OR WOOD CHOP as it should have been advertised!  Bottom line for this restaurant:  Everything is made to look like Fine Dining however when you take the wrapper off this experience you find out that this is a slick ripoff, complete with a smooth talking car salesman/restaurant manager named Kyle. The food is precooked and reheated....you can not ask for a specific meat temperature and the fish is tough and bleeding water which indicated frozen and reheated. Lastly they automatically apply a 18% gratuity to the check and then ask for an additional gratuity. APPALLING based upon our experience.  TAKE MY CONSIDERED ADVISE....SAVE YOUR MONEY EAT AT HOME BEFORE YOU COME TO THE THEATER!  The EXPERIENCE is very similar to a BAD CRUISE LINE or most weddings.  Perhaps Executive Chef Edward Steinhoff should pay more attention to food quality. Maybe supervision over the four restaurants at the Straz Center is too big of a job for him.  Also there is no public records of his Executive Chef credentials nor any culinary training he may have graduated.  I was unaware that the Brooklyn New York Boiler Mechanic Union gave cooking lessons or for that matter owning a deli catering company qualifies a person to hold an EXECUTIVE CHEF designation?  This place has the potential to be Great however the kitchen needs to be MUCH tighter.

Maestro's Cafe is a great location to eat before a show but don't expect a good meal or any food on the buffet.  The buffet was COMPLETELY empty.  We got there at 6p which gave us 1.5hr to eat before the show and they scarcely restocked the food when it ran out.  Even the carving station gentleman looked embarrassed.  And forget about any desert!  That never got restocked. New to the theatre we had hoped we found a hidden gem but forget about it. We spent $250 (4 buffet dinners and 2 cocktails/pp) to pick at an empty buffet.
I attended an entertainment venue but not sure I would come back due to the acoustics, otherwise it was a nice place for dining.
Awesome place. Delicious food. Highly recommended
Great experience, nice preshow bar and restaurant.
The place was very nice. However the dance floor tiles are coming up and they should be replaced before someone gets hurt.
Their food was phenomenal. Attended a wonderful event there. Beautiful accommodations!
What a nice surprise! Open before performances. Food and service very nice. Upscale.
Two tasteless burgers for 26.00 Music and environment peaceful.  They really need to beef up the food.  I'm not even a picky eater,  but the food is over priced,  not even chips,  fries or a pickle.
Only had drinks at bar.
Such a romantic place, my husband brought me here once for a date and I enjoy every second of my stay, the food, the place the ambiance everything seems perfect. highly recommended.
Very good food I would drive an hour to eat this.

Service was great, but the food was extremely underwhelming. I got the ribeye, it was nice and chewy. It reminded of a “steak n eggs” kinda steak you’d get at a diner. My gf got salmon, boy was it dry. Our sides were very bland and unappetizing. The apple pie had a cafeteria feel to it. It was very disappointing. The salad bar was pretty good though. It’s a set menu with a limited selection at $46/person. Our bill was $134 after tip... we only had water and coffee to drink, zero alcohol.

Very good visit.  Attentive but not obtrusive waiter. Soup and salad bar very good. Chocolate Espresso Martini excellent.  Steak well prepared. Overall great experience! Had been disappointed a couple of visits ago overdone steak/dried out overcooked fish on a visit last year but Maestro's seems to have returned to the norm that being a good venue and value for preshow dining. Desert which was included was a small portion of rum flavored cake.  Good, but could have been better!

A wonderful dining experience prior to a show or for a date night. Excellent service from staff. Everyone was kind and attentive. The menu was a clever play of Hamilton for the show run. The food was superb!

Maestro's was a nice place to grab a bite to eat.  However, it was a bit more than I expected if they were to drop the price to around $30 per person I would have given them a 5☆ review.  In my opinion the food was just "okay" and nothing to write home about.
Disappointed.
Delicious food and excellent staff
Food and selection was excellent! Made for a perfect night at the theater!
Great food and very welcoming atmosphere. The service here is exceptional and great for hosting a celebration or special occasion.
Excellent food and the restauraunt is set up to allow you to hang out until your performance time no matter what time your dinner seating was.

I planned a special Holiday surprise for my adorable date, and we kicked off the evening with a meal at Maestro's restaurant in Tampa. Maestro's is the high-end restaurant adjacent to the Straz Center for the Performing Arts, which features premier tableside service. Chef Edward Steinhoff had created a unique menu to complement the show, and since we were planning to see "An American in Paris" following dinner, we knew that we'd be enjoying a fine French-inspired meal.  The restaurant was decorated for the Holidays with festive trees and colorful seasonal greenery. After being seated, our server, Alix, helped me to select a delicious bottle of 2013 Argentinian Mairena Malbec. That's not a vintage which you'll likely see in Tampa, and Alix said that they only had a few bottles left in their cellar. It was delicious, and I'm very glad that we had the chance to enjoy a bottle.  The meal starts with a visit to the Antipasti table, located in the middle of the dining room. Each night Maestro's features two different soups, and a wide variety of gourmet salads, fresh and fire-roasted vegetables, seasonal fruits, artisan cheese, charcuterie, and rustic breads and crackers. Yum!  For my main course, I ordered the Chef's Local Catch, and that turned out to be pan-seared grouper with a light lemon cream sauce, which was served with roasted vegetables and rice pilaf. Very delicious, and not too heavy.  After clearing the plates, Alix was back with the dessert tray, and I got talked into a light and flakey French pastry, layered with heavy cream and raspberries. It was delicious and extremely decadent.  For the record, the dinner is prix fixe, meaning all of the meals on the menu are offered at a fixed price, and that includes your visit to the Antipasti table, along with your choice of main course, and dessert. Wine and kisses were extra!  Candace and I really enjoyed our dinner, and thought this was the perfect opening act for a night at the theater. The hostess very kindly took a photo of us standing in front of the Christmas tree in their lobby before we dashed next door to see the show.
yum

Nice place near the Stratz theater for meal prior to a show. The pricing is fixed based on have a full meal (with desert) or a soup, salad bar (with desert). The food was delicious and the staff attentive. They offer a decent selection of wines and mixed drinks. Recommend you make reservations.
Very nice place
Awesome orchestra!
I don't eat at the restaurant it's a club on Saturday nights for Latin dancing great fun best Place in Tampa
Great place
Very nice venue, however the dance floor is very uneven.
Awesome eats great talented chefs brilliant experience!

My dinner tonight was outstanding:  local snapper with a Parmesan crust over a sweet potato mash with asparagus. The snapper was so soft it was like butter!  The sweetness of the mash was a wonderful contrast. And their soup and salad bar was excellent as always. I had the seafood bisque which had a lot of sherry - nothing wrong with that!  Considering the meal includes the salad bar and the dessert, the price is well worth it!
We went for Mother's Day brunch - excellent service and great brunch! Glad we made reservations, we will absolutely go again.
Love this place!

We had a wonderful time.  The waiter was attentive.  The buffet salad bar was well stocked and our meal was great.  It was our 36th Anniversary and the waiter must have told the chef because my chocolate dessert (meant to resemble Alps because we were seeing The Sound of Music) came with a sweet Happy Anniversary message.
Went on mother's day.  It was great food,  service and atmosphere

They sell very delicious food, there are usually many people and sometimes you can't find places but you don't have to wait long, you get good treatment from waiters and the prices are flexible, highly recommended.

Mediocre at best.  Salad bar and soup buffet was ok and then the meal went down hill from there. Steak was overcooked, waitress was friendly but unhelpful, desserts were inedible.  Hopefully the show will be better.
Excellent service and attention to detail for celebrations!
Food was very good, service fast and efficient. They made sure we were finished well before curtain time.
Food was great, nice to be next door to the Straz when you are going to a performance.  Good service, good food - I recommend.

They ruined our evening. Even though we reserved a table in the main restaurant they said they were overbook and offered us a seat at the bar. Completely ridiculous, will never visit this place again.

The price does not match the quality. I would not recommend this place if you like your food to taste good. There are too many restaurants within walking distance of the Straz to waste your money on this place.
Nothing to say but that you need to go.
A crap meal at absurd prices, go somewhere else it is nothing but highway robbery.  $12.00 for a mixed drink, 50.00 for a chicken dinner, the menu has no prices on it, what's with that???????
Incredibly convenient if you're going to a Straz event.  But the quality doesn't always justify the high prices.
